    "caption": "🤩 Gym to Crag Across LA 🤩\n\nLast week, we wrapped up three Gym to Crag events at @cliffsofid, @class5gym, and @thepostclimbing. The turnout was incredible—huge crowds, great energy ⚡️, and thoughtful conversations all around.\n\nEach event included:\n\n 💜 The @bishopclimbingrangers\n 💜 An @accessfund Climbing Steward from Red Rock\n 💜 A @joshuatreenps National Park Ranger\n 💜 @joshuatreefriends\n\nFrom tabling to casual one-on-one chats to interactive Gym to Crag trivia, the nights were complete with drinks, snacks, prizes, insightful questions 🙋‍♀️, participatory learning, and meaningful connections. \n\nConsidering the importance of stewardship and responsible recreation, we covered climbing history, ecology, geology, and Leave No Trace principles specific to Bishop, Joshua Tree, and Red Rock. Many participants shared that they learned a ton about outdoor climbing ethics, land management, and access issues. \n\nWith indoor climbing continuing to be the fastest-growing entry point into the sport, events like these play a key role in helping climbers feel informed, prepared, and excited to take their climbing outside responsibly.\n\nThanks to everyone who came out 🙌—we’re stoked to keep building these connections from gym to crag.\n\n#laclimbing #class5climbing #cliffsofid #thepostclimbing #touchstoneclimbing",
